						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Maybe you meant MMC3 (mapper 4)?</div><br />Ah yes, mmc3. That's it.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"> Either way, WRAM isn't absolutely necessary for handling compressed maps, there are plenty of other options: on-the-fly decompression from ROM, partial decompression (only the part of the map that surrounds the player needs to be in RAM), and so on. But if you want to go with WRAM, that's a valid choice. It will make the cartridges more expensive though, in case you ever decide to manufacture them.</div>
<br />good point. I'd like to have the option to reproduce the end product when the time comes, but I also really want to have destructable backgrounds. I guess I just need to weigh my options.</div>

